# App Config

## Single Source of Truth

All app metadata lives in `packages/app-config/src/config.ts`. **Never hardcode** app names, descriptions, colors, URLs, or branding in individual apps.

## What Lives in the Config

- App name, slug, description, version
- Brand colors (primary, secondary)
- URLs (website, API, docs, support email)
- Social links (GitHub, Twitter, Discord)
- Mobile identifiers (bundle ID, deep link scheme)
- SEO metadata (OG image, keywords)

## How to Use

### In TypeScript apps (web, admin, server)

Import directly:

```typescript
import { appConfig } from "@repo/app-config";
```

- `apps/web/src/app/layout.tsx` — uses `appConfig.name`, `appConfig.description`
- `apps/admin/src/app/layout.tsx` — uses `appConfig.name` with "Admin" suffix
- `apps/server/src/app.ts` — uses `appConfig.name`, `appConfig.version`, `appConfig.urls.api`

### For JSON configs and assets (react-native, docs)

Run `pnpm sync-config` after editing the config. This:

- Patches `apps/react-native/app.json` (name, slug, scheme, bundleId, colors)
- Patches `apps/docs/mint.json` (name, colors, URLs, socials)
- Generates `theme.css` for web and admin (full OKLCH light/dark palette from primary color)
- Copies logo/favicon/icon assets from `packages/app-config/assets/` to all apps

## Brand Assets

All logos, favicons, and icons live in `packages/app-config/assets/`:

- `logo-light.svg` / `logo-dark.svg` — brand logos
- `favicon.svg` — favicon
- `icon-512.png` / `icon-192.png` — app icons (mobile + PWA)
- `splash.png` — mobile splash screen

## Rules

- **DO** import `appConfig` from `@repo/app-config` for any app identity reference
- **DO** run `pnpm sync-config` after changing config or assets
- **DO NOT** hardcode "Mastermind" or any app name in component files
- **DO NOT** manually edit `apps/web/src/app/theme.css` or `apps/admin/src/app/theme.css` — they are generated
- **DO NOT** manually edit brand assets in `apps/*/public/` or `apps/docs/logo/` — they are copied from the config package
